                <h2>Changing tools</h2>

                <p>In 2019 Help Scout moved from Sketch to Figma. I could write a Medium post (or seven) on these two tools' advantages and disadvantages. One place where Figma shines, however, is its plugins. Easy to find and install, but also easy to create.
                    I've written several since the plugin store launched within Figma last year. Some are internal, centered around Help Scouts design system, <a href="https://style.helpscout.com/product/#help-scout-design-system" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener"
                        class="c-work__out-link"><span>HSDS</span></a>, and some are used by thousands of designers worldwide.
                </p>

